# LICENSE (Research / Non-Commercial)

**Short version:** You may use this repository for **research and non-commercial purposes** with **attribution**.  
Commercial use is **not permitted** without a separate license from the authors.

This repository uses a simple two-part model so it all fits in one file:

- **Code (firmware, scripts, tools)** → **PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0**  
  *Allows use, modification, and distribution for non-commercial purposes; commercial use requires a separate commercial license.*  
  Canonical text: <https://polyformproject.org/licenses/noncommercial/1.0.0/>

- **Content (documentation, figures, CAD/hardware design files, data)** → **Creative Commons Attribution–NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)**  
  *Allows sharing and adaptation for non-commercial purposes with attribution.*  
  Canonical text: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode>

> This project is **not open source** under OSI definitions due to the non-commercial restriction.
> If you need commercial rights, contact the maintainers for a separate license.

---

## Attribution

When you use or adapt this work for research/non-commercial purposes, please include:

```
CLINCH — Laminar-Shear Biogel Closure System
Copyright (c) 2025 <Your Name>
Used under PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0 (code) and CC BY-NC 4.0 (content).
https://github.com/<your-org>/clinch
```

If your venue supports **SPDX** headers, use:

- Code: `// SPDX-License-Identifier: PolyForm-Noncommercial-1.0.0`
- Docs/Designs/Data: `% SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-NC-4.0` or `# SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-NC-4.0`

---

## Scope

- **“Commercial use”** means any use intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
- **“Research / non-commercial”** includes academic research, teaching, personal experimentation, and evaluation.

If in doubt, **open an issue** or email `<license@yourdomain>`.

---

## Trademarks & Safety

- The **“CLINCH”** name and any logos are **not** licensed as trademarks.
- This repository contains **research prototypes** only; **not a medical device**. No clinical use without proper approvals.

---

## Full Texts (External References)

To keep this file short and canonical, we reference the official, immutable license texts:

- PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0: <https://polyformproject.org/licenses/noncommercial/1.0.0/>  
- CC BY-NC 4.0 Legal Code: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode>

You may also place copies of these texts under `/LICENSES/` in your repository for archival purposes.
